args: O that which shines like the darn sun!\nI beseech ya, release yer light'n make\nmanifest its brilliance! Onmyo! Haaaah!
Perhaps you're not completely useless\nby yourself after all.
Sorry, what's that, master?\nM'ears are still ringin'.
Bah. I was telling you not to let\none victory go to your fuzzy head!
That there's a right mean thing\nto be sayin'... Hee hee!
What are you grinning about?\nStop that. It creeps me out.
'Member how I said I can't never\nbe like ya, master?
Well, now I feel like if I keep tryin',\none day I WILL be just like ya!
Get that idiotic idea right out of your\nhead. You'll need to do a lot more\nthan this to even approach my level.
Still, ain't no harm in a fox dreamin',\nam I right?
Look, I was just so darn desperate to be\nuseful that I let m'self get carried away.
But I'm a stubborn ol' critter, so I kept right\non tryin'—and that darn near got a lot'a\ngood folk hurt.
So I know there's stuff even an stupid fox\nlike me can do—I just gotta find it.
Anyway, while I look for that, I promise\nnot to cause ya more trouble by tryin' to\nget too big for m'britches.
Exactly—you don't need to be me.\nIf you want to be my assistant, you just\nneed to find ways to be USEFUL.
Sorry to disturb this tender moment.
I came to report to Seimei\nabout the Mukuroshu.
Oh, right. Gozu took 'em all somewhere\nafter we beat 'em down, didn't he?
Yeah. I was hoping we'd be able to get\nsomething useful out of them, but...
But they died before they could talk.
It was not us.\nIt was Doman's curse, presumably.
So you knew this would happen?
Do you really think I would have foreseen\nthis and just let our only leads up and die?
So what's all this chitter and chatter\n'bout some kinda curse?

A curse on his followers that takes their
lives if they ever attempt to reveal
information about him would be a simple
thing for an onmyoji as capable as he.
Those Mukuroshu said they borrowed\nshikigami from Doman, so I'm guessing\nthe curse was placed in that moment.
But how could he do somethin'\nso dang cruel to his own allies?
He doesn't see them as allies any more\nthan a chess master grows fond of pawns.
We dismantled one of their bases;\nthat's enough achievement for one day.
And I helped out my people!
Yeah, I s'pose it's nice the folk here\ndon't need to worry about bein' stolen\nfrom their beds no more.
That reminds me: There's something\nI need to show you, Seimei.
A map? But what do all the numbers\nand symbols represent?

They show trends in the number of people
disappearing in each district. I looked into
it while dealing with all the trouble the
Mukuroshu stirred up.
See how a few of them have weird spikes\ncompared to last year?
Meaning if we follow the spikes,\nwe can find the Mukuroshu.
Can't be sure, but it seems likely.\nBetter than stumbling around in the dark,\nat any rate, so...good luck!
I take it your part in this little adventure\nhas come to a close, then?
Like I said, I just wanted to save\nmy own people.
Traveling miles to help others isn't my\nidea of a good time—I leave THAT to you.
Why do I get the feeling I'm being used...?\nBah. Fine. Have it your way.
What, now?! But we ain't ready!
Then GET us ready!\nThat's an assistant's job!
Yes, master! Right away, master!\nI'll get us readier than a farmer at\nthe first day'a spring!
*sigh* I wish I could trust that.
Never mind. Let's just get going.
Wait for me, Lord Seimei! Waaaaait!
